
Wrapper Class
  Java provides a Wrapper Class for each of its 8 primitive types
  A wrapper class provides simple operations and information about the primitive type

  byte -> Byte       - 1 byte
  short -> Short     - 2 bytes
  char -> Character  - 2 bytes unsigned
  int -> Integer     - 4 bytes
  long -> Long       - 8 bytes
  float -> Float     - 4 bytes
  double -> Double   - 8 bytes
  boolean -> Boolean - 1 byte

  min/ max value
    <Wrapper_Class>.MIN_VALUE
    <Wrapper_Class>Integer.MAX_VALUE
    ex
      Integer.MIN_VALUE

  num of bits
    <Wrapper_Class>.SIZE
    ex
      Integer.SIZE


